      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T03:19:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the way i interpret this is \"if you really know that you reached the end, then you return empty string\".\nif we asked for N and received N, we do not know if we reached the end.\n\nsay [a, b] were returned at the time where only [a, b] existed, but then c is added. if the response did not have page token, the user will never see c\n\ni am not sure it is a violation of the guideline if we don\u0027t know if we reached the end\n\nwdyt?",
      "parentUuid": "bb3b9741_08f703ba",
