      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T05:40:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "yes, and i don\u0027t see anything we can do, or what use case would make us go out of our way to implement something differently. Practically, some system will make a few List calls one after another in a row. In UI case, between page1 is returned and a human clicks on page2 link, many things may change and users won\u0027t be very surprise that new items appeared. I think the strong guarantees we provide take place only after invocation is finalized. Until that happens, new test results may appear here and there, and a single List call returns one snapshot, but a later identical call may return something different",
      "parentUuid": "9fa51d1f_d0a2d54c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 83,
        "startChar": 19,
        "endLine": 83,
